   "source": [
    "Looking at the plot we can see that the highest correlation is seen on the pair of \"drug/narcotics vs warrants\". This is not that surprising, since often a warrant is needed to investigate drug crimes, so it makes sense that they would be correlated. A drug bust is usually commited with the help of the 4th amendment which states that police have to get a warrant because the amendment protects people against unreasonable searches and seizures and generally requires police to obtain a warrant based on probable cause before conducting a search. The least correlated pair is drug/narcotics vs vandalism. This is also not quite surprising as drug/narcotics is usually more commited by a different type of criminal that vandalism, which can somewhat be seen in a number of different types of \"criminals\". Drug/narcotics is often associated with more \"specific\" types of criminals directly involved in drug trade. Vandalism, on the other hand, can be committed by a much wider range of people, from bored teenagers to political activists."
   ]
